Commentary: OUT! LBW! Another excellent review from India! Ravichandran Ashwin strikes now and gets his 100th Test wicket against England. He tosses this one up from around the wicket, on middle and leg, angling away, Jonny Bairstow goes down to sweep it away but misses it completely to get hit on the pads. A huge shout for LBW, but the finger stays down. Rohit Sharma goes for the review. UltraEdge confirms no bat involved and Ball Tracking shows three reds. Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Mohammed Siraj strikes! The bowling change has worked wonders for India and they get a wicket against the run of play here. Siraj pitches this one up again, on middle, swinging in, hint of reverse swing there, Ben Foakes steps across to flick it away, but fails to keep it down and hits it from the inside half of the bat straight into the hands of Ravindra Jadeja at short mid-wicket who makes no mistake. This is tossed up, full and on off, turns in sharply, Shubman Gill prods forward to block but plays down the wrong line, the ball sneaks past the inside edge and hits him on the pads. Commentary: OUT! LBW! Huge appeal and the Umpire raises the finger! Rajat Patidar takes the review. India retain the review but lose the wicket of Rajat Patidar.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! A massive moment in this Test match! India takes a brilliant review here and the centurion from the first innings walks back to the hut now. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes this one quicker through the air from around the wicket, full and turns in a bit, Joe Root stays in his crease and tries to flick it away but yorks himself and misses getting hit on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW, but the finger stays down. Ashwin is quite confident and convinces Rohit Sharma to take the review. UltraEdge confirms no bat involved and the only thing that can save Root is if it has pitched outside leg or wickets is umpire's call, but it is not as Ball Tracking shows three reds. Root is disappointed but will have to go back on just 11 and India will feel they are well in the game now.
Default_Commentary: 16.6: Ravichandran Ashwin to Joe Root, OUT! lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin.
